        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43775",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You are probably overrunning the 32-bit integer used to store the date (ie: # of seconds since Jan 1 1970). Any date past 19.01.2038 03:14:07 ( =2147480047 ) can't be represented in \"epoch time\" using the 32 bit signed integer datatype. \r\nSee: http:\/\/bugs.php.net\/bug.php?id=7103",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-20T09:21:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-20T09:21:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43779",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dillchuk",
                        "name": "dillchuk",
                        "displayName": "Derek Illchuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Indeed yes!\r\n\r\nYet, the documentation of Zends \/Date\/DateObject.php's `mktime` function says:\r\n\r\n\"The timestamp returned by mktime() can exceed the precision of traditional UNIX timestamps, by allowing PHP to auto-convert to using a float value.\"\r\n\r\n\r\nSo, in this case, the documented functionality is breaking.\r\n\r\n\r\nHere's a fix that works for me, although I don't know the ramifications (if any).  You'll notice a lot of effort has gone into the DateTime::mktime function to handle the case of year >= 2038, so my fix simply uses that as a fallback.\r\n\r\n    \/\/ In Date\/DateObject.php\r\n    protected function mktime($hour, $minute, $second, $month, $day, $year, $gmt = false)\r\n    {\r\n        \/\/ complete date but in 32bit timestamp - use PHP internal\r\n        if ((1901 < $year) and ($year < 2038)) {\r\n\r\n            $oldzone = @date_default_timezone_get();\r\n            \/\/ Timezone also includes DST settings, therefor substracting the GMT offset is not enough\r\n            \/\/ We have to set the correct timezone to get the right value\r\n            if (($this->_timezone != $oldzone) and ($gmt === false)) {\r\n                date_default_timezone_set($this->_timezone);\r\n            }\r\n            $result = ($gmt) ? @gmmktime($hour, $minute, $second, $month, $day, $year)\r\n                             :   @mktime($hour, $minute, $second, $month, $day, $year);\r\n            date_default_timezone_set($oldzone);\r\n\r\n            \/**\r\n             * The fix: check that system `mktime` returns something valid.  If not,\r\n             * carry on, it might be better than giving up.\r\n             *\/\r\n            \/\/ return $result;\r\n            if ( $result !== false ) {\r\n              return $result;\r\n            }\r\n\r\n\r\nI hope you give this a fair shake, as it looks like a straightforward fix -- you've heard that before ;)\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dillchuk",
                        "name": "dillchuk",
                        "displayName": "Derek Illchuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-20T15:52:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-20T15:52:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43780",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dillchuk",
                        "name": "dillchuk",
                        "displayName": "Derek Illchuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I just noticed that `mktime` returns -1 (instead of FALSE) prior to PHP 5.1, so that would be:\r\n\r\nif ( $result !== false && $result != -1 ) { return $result; }\r\n\r\n\r\nAll the best,\r\nDerek",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dillchuk",
                        "name": "dillchuk",
                        "displayName": "Derek Illchuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-20T16:56:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-20T16:56:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43781",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}\r\nI just noticed that `mktime` returns -1 (instead of FALSE) prior to PHP 5.1, so that would be:\r\n{quote}\r\nYes but is recommendation of the framework 5.2.4 or later see http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/svn\/framework\/standard\/trunk\/README.txt",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-20T17:19:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-20T17:19:03.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
